---
description: "Protocol interfaces are frozen — read-only contracts"
globs: ["app/protocols.py", "app/types.py"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Protocol interfaces in app/protocols.py are frozen contracts. All Protocol methods that perform I/O MUST be async.

To add a new service: define the Protocol first, get approval, then implement the adapter.

Adapters import and implement Protocols. Application code imports and calls Protocols — never adapters directly.

Protocol method signatures use standard Python types and shared dataclasses from app/types.py.